FORMER Witbank Spurs coach Sammy Troughton has joined Mpumalanga rivals TS Sporting as a technical director. Troughton, who also had a stint as head coach of University of Pretoria, brings a wealth of football knowledge both as a coach and as a player. TS Sporting have never had anyone with experience in all divisions they have played in since the clubâ€™s inception in 2016. Troughton played for Glentoran and Wolverhampton Wanderers before coming to South Africa in 1985 to play for Jomo Cosmos, Mamelodi Sundowns and Orlando Pirates. He joins another former Pirates player at TS Sporting in Benson Mhlongo.  